  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "description",
      "abstract": "Establishes a three-year Health Coverage Continuity Pilot Program to be administered by the Department of Human Services, in consultation with the Department of Commerce and Consumer Affairs, to subsidize the cost of certain health insurance deductibles for eligible individuals.  Authorizes the Department to contract with a nonprofit health insurer or community-based organization to operate the Pilot Program; provided that the Department shall allow the operator to access state-backed reinsurance or risk stabilization support for the operation of the Pilot Program.  Requires reports to the Legislature.  Appropriates funds.  Repeals 6/30/2029.  Effective 7/1/2050.  (SD2)"
    }
  ],
